ENTRY       EC 3.1.15.1                 Enzyme
NAME        venom exonuclease;
            venom phosphodiesterase
CLASS       Hydrolases;
            Acting on ester bonds;
            Exonucleases that are active with either ribo- or deoxyribonucleic acids and produce 5'-phosphomonoesters
REACTION    Exonucleolytic cleavage in the 3'- to 5'- direction to yield nucleoside 5'-phosphates
COMMENT     Preference for single-stranded substrate.
HISTORY     EC 3.1.15.1 created 1978
REFERENCE   1
  AUTHORS   Laskowski, M.
